HEADWORD: Hairs breadth
<hw>Hair's"
breadth`</hw> <pr>(h⟦acir⟧rz"-)</pr></mhw>. <def>The diameter or breadth
of a hair; a very small distance; sometimes, definitely, the
forty-eighth part of an inch.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>hairsbreadth</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every one could sling stones at an <qex>hairbreadth</qex> and not
miss.</q> <rj><qau>Judg. xx. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hairbreadth</ent>⟦br⟧
